              {"format": "Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL) testing verifies the behavior of the firmware by connecting two HaGeneral Boards and simulating interactions. In this setup, connect two HaGeneral boards to test the following serial communication protocols: I2C, SPI, and UART.", "css": "font-size: 1rem;"},
